  "market_context": "NQ daily candle traded down through the previous day low at 20,321.25 and closed back inside the prior day's range, forming a reversal candle with a large lower wick, signalling a potential bullish reversal for the next session.",
  "key_observation": "After the daily reversal candle sweeps previous day low and closes back inside the range, the next day's hourly delivery should respect the upper half of that wick — opening, forming a low, and expanding higher into the highs without violating 0.5 of the wick.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On the NQ daily chart, identify the previous day low at 20,321.25 that was swept and closed back through, creating a large-wick reversal candle.",
    "Step 2: Mark the 0.5 (mean threshold) of the daily candle's lower wick as the level price must respect if it is to trade higher.",
    "Step 3: Drop to the 1H chart to monitor intraday delivery for an open-low-high-close sequence respecting the wick's upper half.",
    "Step 4: Observe price form a low on the hourly, then expand higher into the highs while holding above the 0.5 wick level, confirming the daily reversal.",
    "Step 5: Conclude that the higher time frame daily candle's wick was respected on the lower time frame, validating the reversal projection."
  ],
  "outcome": "Hourly price formed a low, respected the 0.5 wick level, and expanded higher into the highs, confirming the anticipated daily reversal.",
  "lessons": "When a daily candle sweeps a previous day high/low and closes back inside the range with a large wick, the next day's lower-time-frame delivery should respect 0.5 of that wick, providing a precise confirmation framework for daily reversals.",
